Anyway, fast forward to the computer era. Only when I became a digital subscriber did I start doing the puzzle daily, although I had been gifted some books of NYT puzzles, so I gained more experience that way.

If you are enjoying the ride in spite of some bumps in the road, stick with it. Use whatever strategies you need: Google; Wordplay column; dictionary or thesaurus. Your confidence will grow!

